message: "If you use this software or build on the ideas in it, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "Session-Typed Skills: a session-typed static compiler for safe interactions in skills for agents"
authors:
  - family-names: Chen
    given-names: Tzu-Chun
    alias: ginaecho
repository-code: "https://github.com/ginaecho/session-typed-skills"
license: MIT
version: 0.1.0
date-released: "2026-07-02"
keywords:
  - multiparty session types
  - multi-agent systems
  - LLM agents
  - protocol verification
  - Scribble
  - deadlock freedom
  - runtime monitoring
  - agent skills
abstract: >-
  Session-Typed Skills (STJP, the Session-Typed Judge Panel) treats the
  conversation between LLM agents as the artifact to type-check. A
  natural-language intent is drafted into a multiparty session type, validated
  for deadlock-freedom by the Scribble compiler, and statically projected into
  one interaction-safe skill per agent plus a runtime enforcement monitor and
  an execution scheduler derived from the same proof. Benchmarked on real
  Azure AI Foundry agents: catches deadlocks no runtime approach can, prevents
  unauthorized irreversible actions, and cuts agent calls and token cost by
  removing idle-agent polling.
